# Decision Lifecycle

## Purpose

The Decision Lifecycle describes how the major architectural components cooperate to analyse a user's decision.

Unlike the component documents, which describe individual responsibilities, this document describes the overall flow of reasoning from the user's initial prompt to completion.

It is intentionally high-level.

Its purpose is to explain how the architecture behaves rather than how individual components perform their work.

